AGI - Vincenzo&nbsp died; Augustine, the father of the police officer Nino, killed by Cosa Nostra together with his wife Ida Castelluccio, on August 8, 1989. Vincenzo&nbsp; Augustine, born on March 22, 1937, was the courageous father, who had never resigned to the death of his son and daughter-in-law - pregnant a few months - and had immediately denounced the attempts of deceiving linked to the double murder. He had a long white beard that - he said - "would not cut off" until the truth about the mandates of the double murder, silences and above all the depistaggies to the investigations emerged. Vincenzo continued to fight for his son even after his wife's death, Augusta Schiera, in February 2019.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
Of the death of Nino and Ida - for which there were many investigative tracks, of which some totally deceiving - were accused three people, including the boss of Resuttana Nino Madonia, the preferred killer by Toto' Riina, who opted for the short rite and in 2021 was sentenced to life imprisonment, also confirmed on appeal on 5 October. Also that day Vincenzo - accompanied by daughters, grandchildren and his inseparable escort but without any more his wife Augusta - showed up at the justice palace of Palermo.
&nbsp;
<div </div After the sentence, Vincenzo Agostino - with his white beard and the slow but decided step facilitated by a stick - was clearly, as always: "I am satisfied because they have condemned the butcher of my son and daughter. Satisfied also for my wife, I wanted her to be there with me. Now I will remove the writing on his stone 'dead waiting for truth and justice'. It is approaching the day when I could cut the beard, because &nbsp; the ordinary procedure is also being completed, in case of conviction I can say that that day I can maintain the promise I made on my son's grave." "Today - he had written on Facebook the month before addressing his wife - we would have celebrated 64 years of marriage. Every second without you is an agony, I miss you infinitely. I will continue to love you, always yours, Vincenzo."
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
The other two defendants - under trial with the ordinary rite - are the boss of the Arenella Gaetano Scotto, accused of the double aggravated murder, and Francesco Paolo Rizzuto, a friend of Nino&nbsp; Augustine, accused of favoring. Also in this procedure Vincenzo - constituted civil part, assisted by lawyer Fabio Repici and with him also daughters, grandchildren and family of Ida Castelluccio, among others - has always wanted to be present, at every hearing, despite the attacks due to age. He will assist from elsewhere in the sentence, being the trial at the final jokes: have already discussed the civil parts, on 3 May and 21 are scheduled the interventions of the defenders of the defendants and then the Court ofassis, chaired by Sergio Gulotta, should retire in the council chamber for the sentence.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2>Nino Augustine, the policeman who hunted the complainants
<br> Nino&nbsp;Agostino&nbsp; was an agent in service at the San Lorenzo Commissioner in Palermo who would also be part of a group that collaborated with the Secret Service for the capture of mafia latients. This would have been the cause of his death determined by What ours. The many depistages to the investigations, also came to light thanks to the perseverance of Vincenzo&nbsp; Augusta Schiera. A moment, important, in this long and tiring battle of truth, was on February 26, 2016, when in the bunker room of the prison Ucciardone there was a dramatic American recognition. Vincenzo recognised in "monkey face" Giovanni Aiello, a former police officer and considered a killer orbiting services and crime: "I did my duty. Now - he said at the end of that day - it touches the judiciary. I recognized a monster face even though he was well made. They were in three for the confrontation, but I immediately recognized him. As I have said in all these years that face is unforgettable." Vincenzo&nbsp; Augustine, in fact, had told the magistrates that a few days before the crime in two had come to look for his son in the house of Carini, they qualified as colleagues and one had a face thrown, as a monster. "Unforgettable", in fact.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2>Don Ciotti, that long beard as suffering
"A long beard as long was the suffering of Vincenzo: 35 years of mourning for a son killed by the mob. It was his distinctive trait, which made us recognize him in the crowd in public events and meetings. That beard we want today to remember as the sign of the constancy of Vincenzo, of his determination to seek truth and justice for his son, his daughter and their child never born. The choice not to cut the beard, until he had obtained clear answers from the state, over the years made it a symbolic figure in the eyes of many other people in the same situation". He declares it in a note Don Luigi Ciotti, President Libera.
"Behold - he writes - we all hope that the long, unbearable wait has not been vain. In a few weeks will close the last of the processes still in progress on the murder Agostino, after some convictions have already been issued. Our greeting to Vincenzo is made less bitter by the awareness that the result pursued for all these years is finally at hand. And from the gratitude we feel because, through his example, many other people and families have found the strength to transform suffering memory into a commitment of hope," he adds.&nbsp;
